description: From the pages of DARK AVENGERS-Bullseye cuts loose! The media knows him only as Hawkeye--but we know he's really the psychopath named Bullseye! How does the world's deadliest assassin fit in with Norman Osborn's hand-picked team of public do-gooders? What's his agenda, and how does it instantly jeopardize the entire Avengers legacy? And how long can the most ruthless killer ever to walk the Earth be kept on a leash? The one-two punch of writer Andy Diggle (THUNDERBOLTS) and Tom Raney (SECRET INVASION: INHUMANS) unite for the solo mini-series that puts the innocent right in the angry archer's crosshairs! description: Peter Parker has a lot to be hopeful about. The Spider-Man is the beloved town hero; President Franklin D. But all is not well in 1934 America - dark forces are at play in the world, and a power vacuum in New York crime is quickly - and violently - being filled! Now Spider-Man must contend with a vicious new breed of killers, criminals, and maniacal death-dealers, reimagined from some of the greatest and deadliest foes of the Spider-Man! description:
Chapter 1

Christmas Eve sees our vampire Tobias Esque sleeping in a subway station only to be rudely awakened by the changing bell of Waldo, a dark skinned, charity collecting Santa. Recognizing each other Waldo smiles at the angry Esque who shouts he's going to kill him. Waldo lucks out and jumps onto a train making good his escape. Esque starts to reminiss about their first encounter.

While killing a wino Waldo had stumbled on the scene and nonchalantly said he had it coming and walked away and for the first time Esque failed to kill someone who saw him feeding.

His mind wanders to the last time he fed. It was the night before thanksgiving and he came across a beautiful blonde woman drinking herself into a state of oblivion looking for self-destructive revenge on the man who was keeping her as his mistress while spending thanksgiving with his family. She takes him back to her flat and instead of sleeping with her he slits her throat and drains her body in an ecstasy of feeding that, like a drug, sends him on a flight of fancy with the blood angel.

With the bars crowded at Christmas Esque stalks the clubs till he finds a suitable location and victim. A girl he singles out a likely target with practiced skill he waits for her to use the bathroom where he will seduce, attack and leave her and make good his escape. She takes so long to use the bathroom Esque has to go himself and on returning finds she has company and is therefore a bad choice.

He then tries a department store and waits in the bathroom but no one shows as they are in too much of a hurry to pay for their consumer items and leave.

Frustrated Esque attends mass at a cathedral and forms a new plan to slake his thirst.

Chapter 2

Esque arrives at Sally's home. Sally is a slightly plump goth girl he met in a club 9 months ago, who took him home, and bit her drinking her blood which made her orgasm over and over.

She opens the door and is overjoyed he remembered her party, much to his dismay, she introduces him has her boyfriend. He takes her aside and tries to get her to goto the bedroom with him so he can feed but she wants the party to end first. He laments he cannot kill her now as her friends have seen him and she even knows his first name.

He thinks back to his favorite Christmas gift as a boy. His mother bought him the Beatles White Album which caused an argument that lasted all day between his parents so he spent the day reading the lyrics and studying the artwork instead.

In the flats kitchen his line of thought is interrupted when Dark Ivory enters and asks if his or thinks he is a vampire. He says he is and she continues to ask him about his biting and non-love making with Sally. Sally enters and Esque takes her to the bedroom in a hurry where she demands he make love to her and not just bite her. Unfortunately Esque is heterosexual but impotent and sex has little meaning for him anymore.

He makes an excuse that he has to go out and will be back. Before he leaves he notices Sally has a gift for him under her tree. His first gift since he was bitten 26 years ago. He laments the fact he will never see her again as Sally watches him leave with a hopeful face.

Chapter 3

Esque finds hims self back in the underground now dejected and hoping for anything to come by that he can feed on with safety. As the station quiets down he recognizes a voice and sees Waldo leading a boy he found at a hospital down into the tunnels. Esque follows and just as Waldo is about to pounce on his prey Esque steps out with knife in hand. Waldo offers Esque the boy before dashing onto the tracks and is killed by a passing train. He briefly considers killing the kid but decides its Christmas and ends up taking the kid back to the hospital.

He skulks the corridors of the hospital looking for a victim when he happens on a plasma storage fridge. He bags up the packs and runs from the hospital and down to the track again where he sups on fresh bagged blood until the blood angel comes to him.
name: The Vampire`s Christmas

description: The Ultimate Inhumans debut, two lives are forever changed, you'll never guess who's back and everyone guest-stars in the first-ever Ultimate Annuals! In Ultimate Fantastic Four Annual #1, it's the first appearance of the Ultimate Inhumans! From a hidden race, she came to steal the heart of the FF's youngest member: the beautiful elemental called Crystal! In Ultimate X-Men Annual #1, it's the return of Ultimate Juggernaut! Juggie makes a play for the Gem of Cyttorak, the jewel that will make him truly unstoppable. Only two small things stand in his way: Rogue and Gambit, the new prince and princess of thieves! In Ultimate Spider-Man Annual #1, Spidey goes toe-to-toe with some old foes - and winds up with a new girlfriend! Who is she? Let's just say she has a familiar face. And in The Ultimates Annual #1, if you thought The Ultimates were the only team S.H.I.E.L.D. was creating - you were wrong! Get ready for the next wave of super-soldiers designed to protect America's vital interests. But is this all that Director Nick Fury is up to, or is there much more to this ultra-clandestine program? And can even S.H.I.E.L.D. keep all these super-people under control? Collects Ultimates Annual #1; Ultimate Fantastic Four Annual #1; Ultimate X-Men Annual #1; Ultimate Spider-Man Annual #1.
name: Ultimate Annuals: Volume One

description: In Ultimate Fantastic Four Annual #2, something strange has happened at Nursery Two, the Baxter Building's Think Tank counterpart in Oregon. It's disappeared, seemingly swallowed up by the earth itself! And if you think that heralds the return of the macabre Mole Man, go to the head of the class! In Ultimate X-Men Annual #2, Dazzler has awakened from her coma only to discover her life is in deadly peril! And even her former fellow X-Men may be powerless to save her as a betrayal within the ranks has left them shellshocked. In Ultimate Spider-Man Annual #2, Punisher and Daredevil return! While Foggy Nelson offers Spidey some legal advice, Police Captain Jean DeWolfe gives him some other advice - on how to take down the Ultimate Kangaroo! And in The Ultimates Annual #2, as the Ultimates clear the wreckage from the recent attack on the United States, a monstrous evil from the past rises from the ashes to launch an attack when America is at her weakest. And with the ranks of the Ultimates severely depleted, all that stands in the path of the long-thought-dead bio-fanatic Arnim Zola is the indomitable Sentinel of Liberty, Captain America, and Sam Wilson, the high-flying Falcon! Collects The Ultimates Annual #2, Ultimate Fantastic Four Annual #2, Ultimate X-Men Annual #2 and Ultimate Spider-Man Annual #2.
name: Ultimate Annuals: Volume Two

name: Violent Messiahs : Genesis

description: In the far future, with the galaxy divided between interstellar superpowers on the brink of war, a desperate officer of the Earth-based Galactic Union sends five maverick pilots on a bizarre mission: bring back the legendary war machine called Voltron. Journeying to distant planet Arus, Keith, Lance, Sven, Hunk and Pidge discover the first clue in the centuries-old mystery - a clue in the shape of a huge mechanical lion.
name: Revelations

description: After crash-landing on Planet Arus, Keith, Sven, Lance, Hunk and Pidge discover the legend of Voltron is real when they find one of the fabled robotic Lions. But after a Supremacy patrol squadron makes the same discovery, a race against time unfolds as the five pilots struggle to beat the Drules to the other four lions hidden beneath the planet's surface. Will the pilots learn the secret of controlling the legendary Lions? Find out in part two of "Revelations."

"Revelations": Chapter 3 The myth has been proven real: the legendary mechanical lions believed to make up the body of Voltron do exist. But when a squadron of Drule warships suddenly attacks, will Keith, Lance, Sven, Hunk and Pidge be able to "use" the Lions... or will they be defeated before they can even begin? Learn the answer - - and witness the beginning of the terrible price Sven will pay.

With a few moments to breathe, Keith and the rest of his team try to learn more about Arus and its situation, even as Sven lies in a coma. But their respite is all too brief, as they receive a visit from Zarkon's son, Prince Lotor ? and to their horror, see a gigantic Coffin ship arrive, bearing one of Hagar's dreaded Robeasts. Will Sven awaken in time for the five pilots to stop the threat? Witness the first sign of Voltron's true return, in Chapter 4 of "Revelations."

The moment of truth has arrived: a gigantic, horrendously destructive Robeast has landed on Planet Arus, and the only way Keith, Hunk, Lance, Pidge, and Sven can defeat it is by resurrecting the legendary Voltron. But will they be able to do that with so much at stake? And even if they can, will it cost them their sanity... or their lives? Find out as "Revelations" concludes!

Fans will recognize the familiar characters, but now writer Dan Jolley and artists Mark Brooks and Clayton Brown introduce these characters with origins never before seen. Find out how the five maverick pilots were chosen for the mission to bring back the legendary war machine called Voltron... and how a distant alien princess knew they were coming.
name: Revelations: A Prologue
